# REST API Basics

## What is REST API?

REST (Representational State Transfer) is a method for communication between client and server using HTTP.

---

## HTTP Methods

| Method | Purpose               |
| ------ | --------------------- |
| GET    | Retrieve Data         |
| POST   | Create Data           |
| PUT    | Update Entire Record  |
| PATCH  | Update Partial Record |
| DELETE | Delete Data           |

